    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen launching neovim, most of the time it will show a very small window only to get remapped after a few milliseconds... I fixed this by setting the columns and lines in neovim configuration:\r\n\r\n```\r\nvim.opt.columns = 272\r\nvim.opt.lines = 56\r\n```\r\n\r\nIMO, the user should not have to directly add the terminal columns and lines to its configuration and neovim should know right from the start how many columns and lines the terminal has.\r\n\r\nHow it looks at launch:\r\n\r\n![ss_2024_06_07_11_43_14](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/14960414/89cbeb60-dda3-4a60-9882-626b04719b30)\r\n\r\nAfter launch:\r\n\r\n![ss_2024_06_07_11_43_27](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/14960414/62ccff77-1625-497e-9955-b303c7dc5821)\r\n\r\nI first reported the issue on foot's codeberg issues but quickly realized this was a problem with neovim:\r\n\r\n[https://codeberg.org/dnkl/foot/issues/1733](https://codeberg.org/dnkl/foot/issues/1733)\r\n\r\nApparently this is because neovim doesn't use SIGWINCH properly:\r\n\r\n[https://codeberg.org/dnkl/foot/issues/453](https://codeberg.org/dnkl/foot/issues/453)\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nUse a very fast terminal like foot or alacritty and you will notice it when launching neovim.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nI would expect neovim to map its window correctly to the terminal lines and columns at launch.\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.11.0-dev-196+g2ce4a4d91e Build type: Release LuaJIT 2.1.1716656478\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nI don't have vim installed\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch Linux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nfoot version: 1.17.2 +pgo +ime +graphemes -assertions\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nfoot\n\n### Installation\n\nArch User Repository (AUR)",
