            "body": "I'm not exactly sure but I'd say it's definitely related. The problem with having to set the lines and columns in the neovim configuration files is that if you open a different size of terminal the UI gets all messed up. I would rather let neovim figure out the terminal's size at launch and set its UI properly instead of flashing a small UI and then expanding to the real size of the terminal.\r\n\r\nIt's not a show stopper but a proper solution is needed IMO. ",
